15/04/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament Speaker Vladimir Seks welcomed Romanian counterpart Adrian Nastase to Zagreb on Thursday (14 April). 
They pledged to improve co-operation between their institutions, especially in the field of EU integration.
Also Thursday, Croatian President Stipe Mesic kicked off a two-day official visit to Norway where he met with Prime Minister Kjell Magne Bondevik and Crown Prince Haakon. 
They agreed on the need to boost economic links. 
(Vecernji List - 15/04/05; HINA - 14/04/05)
